DOCiD - Environment Configuration Guide

This project now uses template-first environment management.

1) Root stack env (Docker Compose)
- Template: `.env.example`
- Runtime file: `.env` (local/server, untracked)
- Purpose: ports, database connection, backend/frontend service wiring.

Setup:
- Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
- Fill required values (especially secrets and credentials)

Example:
- `cp .env.example .env`

2) Frontend env (single shared template)
- Template: `frontend/.env.example`
- Runtime file used by frontend: `frontend/.env` (untracked)

Setup:
- Any environment: `cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env`
- Fill required values (client secrets, SMTP creds, etc.)

3) Security rules
- Never commit real credentials.
- Tracked `*.example` files keep keys and non-sensitive defaults only.
- Real env files are gitignored.

4) Port conventions used in current templates
- Frontend host port: `3001`
- Backend host/container port: `5002`
- Postgres host port: `5432` (adjust if needed per server)

5) Typical container startup
- `docker compose --env-file .env up --build -d db redis backend frontend`
- First-time DB init:
  - `docker compose --env-file .env --profile bootstrap up --build backend-bootstrap`
